(fifthQuint)Alogliptin Tablets Special Drug Use Surveillance "Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus: Monotherapy/Combination Therapy With -GI".

 A special drug use surveillance is planned to examine the safety and efficacy of long-term use of alogliptin in patients with type 2 diabetes mellitus under the daily clinical use conditions.

 Participants of this surveillance will be patients with type 2 diabetes mellitus who failed to respond adequately to diet therapy and exercise therapy alone or to a combination of diet therapy, exercise therapy, and -glucosidase inhibitor.

 The planned sample size is 3,000 subjects.

 The usual adult dosage for oral use is 1 alogliptin tablet (25 mg) once daily.

